    <etym xml:lang="ru">Общеиндоевропейский глагол. Основа выступает в древнеиранском в нескольких
        видах: %ipṛs-%i, %ipars-%i, %ifras-%i. Осетинский отражает форму %ipars-%i. Ср. <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pursīdan : purs-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
                ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>pursītan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"
                ><lang/><w>pirsīn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hac"
            ><lang/><w>pärs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"
            ><lang/><w>pursaγ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"
            ><lang/><w>pušt-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"
            ><lang/><w>pərs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
            ><lang/><w>pṛs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
            ><lang/><w>pörs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"
            ><lang/><w>pörs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"
            ><lang/><w>pešc-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
        ><lang/><w>paws-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/><w>pīs</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/><w>f%rə%rros-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>purs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>*ā-pṛs-(ʼʼprs-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                ><lang/><w>puls-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>pərəs-, pars-,
                fras-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>pars-,
            fras-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>praś-,
                    pṛččh-</w><gloss><q>спрашивать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><w>prččháti</w><gloss><q>он спрашивает</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>просити, прашати</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><lang/><w>просить, с-праш-иватъ, во-прос, во-прош-ать</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="lt"
            ><lang/><w>praszу́ti</w><gloss><q>требовать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="lt"><w/><gloss><q>просить</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="got"
                ><lang/><w>fraihnan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><lang/><w>fragen</w><gloss><q>спрашивать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="de"><w>forschen</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>исследовать</q></gloss></mentioned>,
        , <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>posco</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
                ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>я
            требую</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>precor</w><gloss><q>я
                    прошу</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                ><w/><gloss><q>молю</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                ><lang/><w>harcanem</w><gloss><q>я спрашиваю</q></gloss></mentioned>. Значение
        ‘читать’ (наряду с основным ‘спрашивать’) весьма древнее; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                ><lang/><w>pati-parsāhy</w><gloss><q>ты прочитаешь</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>pat-purs</w><gloss><q>читать</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><biblScope>Herzfeld. Paikuli, 237</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>pt-βs</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>читать</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru"
                >XXXI 71 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">XXXI 71 ff.</biblScope></bibl>).
        Все приведенные четыре значения совмещаются и в некоторых кавказских языках: <mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>kʼitxva</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"
                ><lang/><w>kʼitxiri</w><gloss><q>спрашивать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="xmf"><w/><gloss><q>читать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>передавать привет</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="xmf"><w/><gloss><q>ворожить</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Ср. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_xyncfarst"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                46</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>65</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">A common Indo-European verb. The base appears in ancient Iranian in several
        forms: %ipṛs-%i, %ipars-%i, %ifras-%i. Ossetic reflects the form %ipars-%i. Cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>pursīdan : purs-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
                ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>pursītan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"
                ><lang/><w>pirsīn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="hac"
            ><lang/><w>pärs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"
            ><lang/><w>pursaγ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"
            ><lang/><w>pušt-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"
            ><lang/><w>pərs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
            ><lang/><w>pṛs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
            ><lang/><w>pörs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"
            ><lang/><w>pörs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"
            ><lang/><w>pešc-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""
        ><lang/><w>paws-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="yah"><lang/><w>pīs</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/><w>f%rə%rros-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>purs-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><lang/><w>*ā-pṛs-(ʼʼprs-)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                ><lang/><w>puls-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>pərəs-, pars-,
                fras-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>pars-,
            fras-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>praś-,
                    pṛččh-</w><gloss><q>ask</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><w>prččháti</w><gloss><q>he asks</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>просити, прашати</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><lang/><w>просить, с-праш-иватъ, во-прос, во-прош-ать</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>praszу́ti</w><gloss><q>demand</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="lt"><w/><gloss><q>ask</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="got"
                ><lang/><w>fraihnan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><lang/><w>fragen</w><gloss><q>ask</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="de"><w>forschen</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>examine</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>posco</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="">
                ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>я
            требую</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>precor</w><gloss><q>I am
                    asking</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>I am
                    praying</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                ><lang/><w>harcanem</w><gloss><q>I am asking</q></gloss></mentioned>. The meaning
        ‘read’ (along with the main meaning ‘ask’) is rather ancient; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                ><lang/><w>pati-parsāhy</w><gloss><q>you will read</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>pat-purs</w><gloss><q>читать</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><biblScope>Herzfeld. Paikuli, 237</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>pt-βs</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>читать</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><author>Benveniste</author><ref target="#ref_BSL"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru"
                >XXXI 71 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">XXXI 71 ff.</biblScope></bibl>).
        All these four meanings are combined in some Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><lang/><w>kʼitxva</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"
                    ><lang/><w>kʼitxiri</w><gloss><q>ask</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="xmf"><w/><gloss><q>read</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>convey greetings</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="xmf"><w/><gloss><q>tell fortunes</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Cf. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_xyncfarst"/>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                46</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>65</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
